HEADWORD: heatstroke
<hw>heatstroke</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A physiological disturbance
caused by exposure to excessive heat, resulting in rapid pulse, hot dry
skin, and fever, leading to loss of consciousness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

